Former governor of Anambra State, Peter Obi, has explained reasons for attending the ceremony where former Vice President Atiku Abubakar officially declared his interest in the presidency of Nigeria. Atiku had formally declared his intention to contest the 2023 presidential election in Abuja on Wednesday at a well-attended event. JUST-IN: Peter Obi Joins 2023 Presidential Race Speaking with Channels Television at the event, the former running mate to Atiku in the 2019 elections, said he play politics with a difference. Asked why he was at the event, given he was eyeing the same position, Obi said, “This is a new politics. I play politics differently. For me, politics is not a war. It’s a relationship. “Atiku is my leader, my boss and a senior brother. If he invites me for anything I will attend. “Aspiring does not say I should not keep my relationships very cordial. “I’m aspiring. Remember, I always say it, Atiku is a unifier. He believes in Nigeria. He’s a good man. And anytime he invites me for anything, I will be there.”